  "response": "The data consumption for streaming a song on the Gaana app can vary depending on the audio quality you've selected. Generally, streaming a single song can consume approximately:\n\n1. Low quality: Around 0.5 MB - 1 MB per song\n2. Medium quality: Around 1 MB - 2 MB per song\n3. High quality: Around 3 MB - 5 MB per song\n\nThe exact data usage will depend on factors like:\n- Song length\n- Selected audio quality\n- Your internet connection\n- Streaming settings in the app\n\nTo minimize data usage, you can:\n- Choose lower audio quality\n- Download songs for offline listening\n- Use Wi-Fi when possible\n\nFor precise details, you can check the Gaana app's settings or contact their customer support.",
